#Java Reflection is a process of examining or modifying the run time behavior of a class at run time.

getting instance of class
1. forName() method of class Class
    syntax:
    Class c = Class.forName("packagename.Classname") // even both classes lie in same package
                                                        should pass the fully-qualified name
                                                        for the class (incl. packages)

   It should be used only when qualified name of class is already known.
2. getClass()
    syntax:
    Class c = Object.getClass(); //so euta class ko object pass garera instance create garna milcha and
                                     used if you know the type.

